config.author: Kitchen
config.visualStylePrompt: Siluetas sobre un fondo blanco plano. Sin degradados, sin sombras, sin texturas y sin contornos. Geometría: usa trazos gruesos y consistentes y simplificación geométrica. Todas las extremidades y terminales deben tener puntas redondeadas y vértices suavizados. Composición: representación plana 2D centrada. Usa el espacio negativo (blanco) para definir la separación interna entre formas negras superpuestas (por ejemplo, el espacio entre una cabeza y un torso). Claridad: maximiza la legibilidad y el reconocimiento semántico a escalas pequeñas. Evita cualquier rasgo facial o detalles intrincados. Usa color solo en el elemento distintivo, si es necesario.

geoContext.region: Santiago, Región Metropolitana de Santiago, Chile

nsm_explications.SLICE: someone does something to this thing; because of this, after a short time, this thing is in many parts; these parts are the same kind

rows.prompt: Within the 'pictograma', establish a central composition focusing on the action of fragmentation. Place the 'cutting_surface' as a horizontal baseline at the bottom. Position the 'onion_composite' resting centrally on the 'cutting_surface'. The 'onion_composite' is visually split: the 'solid_onion_body' occupies the left side, while concentric 'detached_slices' are displaced slightly to the right to signify the result of slicing. The 'chef_knife' is positioned vertically, with the 'blade' intersecting the space between the 'solid_onion_body' and the 'detached_slices', visually bridging the cut. The 'hand' enters from the top or top-right, gripping the 'handle' of the 'chef_knife', implying a downward vertical force vector.

nsm_explications.CHOP_IN_SQUARES: I want you to do something to this something. After, I want this something to be inside many small parts. I want all these parts to be the same.

rows.prompt: The 'pictograma' contains a central 'cutting_surface' viewed from a 45-degree isometric angle. The 'cutting_board' forms a rectangular base at the bottom. Resting on the 'cutting_board' is the 'onion_composite'. This object visually transitions from left to right: the left half is a solid 'onion_bulb', while the right half fragments into separated, geometric 'onion_squares' to represent the diced result. The 'action_assembly' interacts directly with the object; the 'knife' is positioned vertically, its blade intersecting the 'onion_composite' at the precise point where the bulb breaks into squares. The 'hand' grips the handle of the 'knife' from above. Vertical 'motion_lines' appear near the blade to emphasize the downward chopping movement.

rows.UTTERANCE: put the pot away in the drawer with the lid upsidedown
rows.prompt: The 'pictograma' depicts a close-up isometric view of a storage action. At the bottom, a 'kitchen_cabinet' extends an 'open_drawer' towards the foreground, revealing an empty interior space ready for storage. Hovering directly above the 'open_drawer', a pair of 'hands' holds a 'pot'. The 'pot' is positioned centrally over the drawer opening. Sitting on top of the 'pot' is an 'inverted_lid', visually distinct by its concave orientation (upside-down). Vertical 'motion_lines' extend downwards from the 'pot' into the 'open_drawer', topologically linking the object to its destination and indicating a downward placing trajectory.

NLU.utterance: put the pot away in the drawer with the lid upsidedown

nsm_explications.UPSIDEDOWN: THE SIDE OF THIS SOMETHING THAT IS ABOVE BEFORE IS NOW BELOW
nsm_explications.PUT_AWAY: YOU MOVE THIS SOMETHING INSIDE ANOTHER SOMETHING

nsm_explications.RUNNY_PREFERENCE: When this thing is inside my body, I want parts of it to move. I want it to be like this. I feel good because of this.

rows.prompt: The 'pictogram' depicts a dining scene centered vertically. The 'diner' is positioned at the top, gazing downward. Below the 'diner', the 'plate' occupies the foreground. Inside the 'plate', the 'scrambled_eggs' form an organic, loose pile. The 'fork' enters the 'scrambled_eggs' from the side or top, lifting a portion slightly. To emphasize the texture, the 'liquid_yolk' appears as a fluid drip or pool connecting the lifted portion on the 'fork' to the rest of the eggs. The 'heart_icon' floats in the negative space near the 'happy_face' of the 'diner', symbolizing preference.
